	<text>
		<body>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The following is the entire speech of <persName>MM Noah</persName>&#44; delivered<lb/> at the laying of the Corner Stone of the <placeName>City of Ararat</placeName>&#44; to<lb/> be located on <placeName>Grand Island</placeName>. It will probably be read with <sic>beco</sic><lb/> interest by all persons feeling a desire to acquaint <del>themselves</del><lb/> with the ancient and modern history of the Jewish nation.</p>
				<p rend="align(center)">SPEECH</p>
				<p>Brothers&#44; Countrymen and Friends</p>
				<p><placeName>N&#126; Y</placeName> EVNG POST&#58; NUMBER 7241 <date>Saturday September 24&#44; 1825</date> No 49 <persName>Williams</persName><lb/> First page begin mid of col 1 and sev sticks on pg 2</p>
				<p><persName>MAJOR NAOH&#39;S</persName> CITY OF REFUGE FOR THE JEWS</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">A corresp of the <placeName>Rochester</placeName> American&#59;<sic>writing</sic> from<lb/> <placeName>Tonawanda</placeName> in this <placeName>State</placeName>&#44; says&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">It was here that <persName>Major M M Noah</persName> attempted to carry<lb/> out his philanthropic purpose of <sic>fndng</sic> a C of R for his scattered<lb/> and <sic>persectd</sic> brethren&#126; A few rods from the riv there stands a little<lb/> brick tower <sic>wh</sic> is fast crumb to ruin&#44; erected by him more than a quart of<lb/> a cent ago. In the eastern wall is <sic>palced</sic> a stone with a Heb inscript<lb/> and the following in English</p>
				<p rend="align(center)">&#8220;<placeName>ARARAT</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(center)">A CITY OF REFUGE FOR THE JEWS</p>
				<p>Founded by <persName>Mordecai Manasseh Noah</persName>&#44; in the month <date>Tizri&#44; 5585</date>.<lb/> <date>September&#44; 1825</date>&#44; and in the 50th year of American Independence&#8221;</p>
				<p>From <placeName>NEW YORK</placeName> DAY BOOK <date>Aug&#44; 1851</date></p>
				<p>All this on pg 96 Ly S Bk Vol 1</p>
